Exercise 2: Pattern Printing
Create patterns using System.out.println():

java
public class Patterns {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("â­ Star Pattern:");
        System.out.println("   *");     // 3 spaces + 1 star
        System.out.println("  ***");    // 2 spaces + 3 stars  
        System.out.println(" *****");   // 1 space + 5 stars
        System.out.println("*******");  // 0 spaces + 7 stars
        
        System.out.println("\nğŸ’– Heart Pattern:");
        System.out.println("  â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸");   // 2 spaces + 3 hearts
        System.out.println("â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸"); // 0 spaces + 5 hearts
        System.out.println("  â¤ï¸â¤ï¸â¤ï¸");   // 2 spaces + 3 hearts
        System.out.println("    â¤ï¸");     // 4 spaces + 1 heart
    }
}
ğŸ§  Understanding the Code
Code Part	What It Does	ğŸ” Explanation
public class HelloWorld	Creates a class	Every Java program needs at least one class
public static void main(String[] args)	Main method	This is where program execution starts
System.out.println()	Prints output	Displays text on the screen
// comment	Adds notes	Ignored by computer, helps humans understand
